<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 06 at 8:58PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Scotland and
southwestern Hoke Counties through 945 PM EDT...
At 858 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles northwest of Laurinburg to near
Minturn. Movement was east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Laurinburg, Raeford, Maxton, Antioch, Wagram, Gibson, East
Laurinburg, Laurel Hill, Camp Mackall and Ashley Heights.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM EDT for
central North Carolina.</instruction>
